TEXT(beginproblem());
$showPartialCorrectAnswers = 1;

$n = random(3,5,1);

$a = random(2,10,1);
$k = random(2,9,1);
if ($k == $a) { 
	$k=$k+1;
}

$b = $a*$k; 

@which = ('first', 'second', 'third');
$tag1 = random(0,2,1);
 
@rc = ('row', 'column');
$tag2 = random(0,1,1);

BEGIN_TEXT

If the determinant of a \($n \times $n\) matrix \(A\) is \(\det\,(A)=$a\), and the matrix \(B\) is obtained from \(A\) by
multiplying the $which[$tag1] $rc[$tag2] by \($k\), then \(\det\,(B)= \) \{ans_rule(5)\}.  

END_TEXT

ANS(num_cmp($b));

